</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33502C489314B32D5CBFBF2FB60FAE6" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B90514F89314B32D5CBFBF2FD77FA92" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1403]" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89314B32D5CBFBF2FE33FBE2" bold="true" box="[199,462,1126,1151]" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The furrow at the base of the rostrum and the connate condition of the tarsal claws are typical of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89314B32D4ADFB1EFDB7FB3E" authorityName="Seidlitz" authorityYear="1891" box="[417,586,1162,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Smicronychini">Smicronychini</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89314B32D76DFB1FFCF9FB3E" authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1935" box="[609,772,1163,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89314B32D76DFB1FFCF9FB3E" box="[609,772,1163,1187]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">Afrosmicronyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other continental Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89314B32D59BFB3AFEC1FB5A" authorityName="Seidlitz" authorityYear="1891" box="[151,316,1198,1223]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Smicronychini">Smicronychini</taxonomicName>
by its femora bearing a strong ventral tooth and its protibiae bearing a distinct ventral tooth or thickening near middle or antemedially. In Madagascar 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89314B32D610FB47FC42FB76" authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1935" box="[796,959,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Afrosmicronyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89314B32D610FB47FC42FB76" box="[796,959,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">Afrosmicronyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from the endemic genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89314B32D59BFB62FEFCFA92" authorityName="Hustache" authorityYear="1920" box="[151,257,1270,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Topelatus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89314B32D59BFB62FEFCFA92" box="[151,257,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">Topelatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
its body length (more than 
<quantity id="4CD7FCAA89314B32D734FB63FD80FA92" box="[568,637,1271,1295]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B90514F89314B32D5CBFA8EFB60FAE6" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1403]" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89314B32D5CBFA8EFEA7FAAE" bold="true" box="[199,346,1306,1331]" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">Life history.</emphasis>
Species whose life histories are documented are associated with hemiparasitic 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89314B32D1FCFA8EFA60FAAE" authorityName="" authorityYear="1799" box="[1264,1437,1306,1331]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="family">Orobanchaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89314B32D5ACFAABFE08FACA" authority=", Anderson &amp; Cox 1997" authorityName=", Anderson &amp; Cox" authorityYear="1997" box="[160,501,1342,1367]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" genus="Striga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89314B32D5ACFAABFF17FACB" box="[160,234,1343,1366]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">Striga,</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE2CBE89314B32D5FEFAAAFE08FACA" author="Anderson" box="[242,501,1342,1367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" refString="Anderson, D. N. &amp; Cox, M. L. (1997) Smicronyx species (Coleoptera: Curculionidae), economically important seed predators of witchweeds (Striga spp.) (Scrophulariaceae) in sub-Saharan Africa. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 87 (1), 3 - 17. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0007485300036300" type="journal article" year="1997">Anderson &amp; Cox 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F2ACC89314B32D70DFAAAFCEFFACA" authority=", Marshall 1940" authorityName=", Marshall" authorityYear="1940" box="[513,786,1342,1367]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" genus="Sopubia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95B8D5D89314B32D70DFAAAFD99FACA" box="[513,612,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="134">Sopubia,</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE2CBE89314B32D760FAAAFCEFFACA" author="Marshall" box="[620,786,1342,1367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="134" refString="Marshall, G. A. K. (1940) The weevils (Col. Curculionidae) of the Chyulu Hills, Kenya. Coleoptera Part 2. The Journal of the East Africa and Uganda Natural History Society, 15, 35 - 73." type="journal article" year="1940">Marshall 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Their larvae develop in seed capsules (forming a gall or not) or in galls on the roots of their host plants. The life history of most species is unknown.
</paragraph>
